(34, 2, '2010-01-21 10:18:15', '2010-01-21 15:18:15', '<strong>A brief update</strong>.  Recently some classmates and I were able to visit our fearless leader, David Sandlin''s studio. See his work <a href="http://www.davidsandlin.com/paintings.html" target="_blank">here </a>\n\nwill be posting more work soon... thanks!<a href="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-31" title="1" src="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/1.jpg?w=300" alt="" width="300" height="225" /></a>\n\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/1.jpg"></a><a href="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-32" title="2" src="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/2.jpg?w=300" alt="" width="300" height="225" /></a>\n\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/2.jpg"></a><a href="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-33" title="3" src="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/3.jpg?w=225" alt="" width="225" height="300" /></a>', 'STUDIO VISIT', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'studio-visit', '', '', '2010-01-21 10:18:15', '2010-01-21 15:18:15', '', 0, 'http://seejbdraw.wordpress.com/2010/01/21/studio-visit/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(623, 2, '2010-02-09 15:43:08', '2010-02-09 20:43:08', '...is it the name of a future space craft? NO! It''s Asset International''s online magazine, a publication i''ve been fortunate enough to do a few images for the past few months.\n\nhere''s one about the "bursting bubble of lumber investments" for the current issue.\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/picture-21.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-38" title="lumber stocks" src="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/picture-21.png?w=300" alt="" width="300" height="123" /></a>\n\nand go <a href="http://www.ai5000.com/ai5000/20100102#pg1" target="_blank">here</a> to see the issue live, with a SICK cover by the savvy genius that is Shout.', 'AI 5000', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ai-5000', '', '', '2010-02-09 15:43:08', '2010-02-09 20:43:08', '', 0, 'http://seejbdraw.wordpress.com/2010/02/09/ai-5000/', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(41, 2, '2010-03-02 14:40:23', '2010-03-02 19:40:23', 'A friend of mine after seeing my work for the first time in many years.\n\n<span style="color:#ff9900;"><em>"I dig your warm palette and I find them pleasantly airy, with just enough of a scratchy sketchy scribble scrable edge, merged with precision, jigglin'' with movement, underlined with optimism, a pinch of slapstick, and jived with humor.  Slam"</em></span>\n\nHA! fun.', 'The ULTIMATE COMPLIMENT', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-ultimate-compliment', '', '', '2010-03-02 14:40:23', '2010-03-02 19:40:23', '', 0, 'http://seejbdraw.wordpress.com/2010/03/02/the-ultimate-compliment/', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(624, 2, '2010-03-02 23:41:31', '2010-03-03 04:41:31', 'well, its been a year in the works but I am FINALLY getting this bad boy out the door.\n\nTertium Comparison is a book of my work illustrating metaphoric quotes, presented in the format of postcards.\n\ndescription from the inside cover:\n\n<span style="color:#ff9900;"><em>"This is a book of translation. My intent is not to introduce you to new quotes but instead make you see them in a new way; a unique view of life lessons we can all take something away from. Through the use of metaphor and contrastive analysis each image overlaps with a quote to bring to life the common message between the two. This overlapping space is known as Tertium."</em></span>\n\n<span style="color:#ff9900;"><em>[gallery columns="2"]\n\n</em></span>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<span style="color:#ff9900;"><span style="color:#888888;">Im proud to be sending this out. I''ve printed a relatively small number of 100, if you are recieving one, I really hope you enjoy.  thanks for reading</span></span>\n\n<span style="color:#ff9900;"><span style="color:#888888;"><em><span style="color:#ff0000;">The books are wrapped in a xerox printed belly band and enclosed in 2 color screen printed cardboard boxes.</span></em></span></span>\n\n<em> </em>\n\n<em> </em>', 'POSTCARD BOOK PROMO', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-long-time-coming', '', '', '2010-03-02 23:41:31', '2010-03-03 04:41:31', '', 0, 'http://seejbdraw.wordpress.com/?p=43', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(625, 2, '2010-03-08 23:25:52', '2010-03-09 04:25:52', '<a href="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/full_w_hands.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-66" title="Tertium Comparison" src="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/full_w_hands.jpg?w=300" alt="" width="300" height="225" /></a>\n\nAs a follow up to my last post, here is a much more comprehensive visual of the promotion book I recently sent out. You can now get a sense of scale, and see all of the illustrations that were used.\n\n<span style="color:#333399;"><strong>Now in VIDEO!! woohoo.</strong></span>\n\n[vimeo vimeo.com/10023990]\n\nThe video can be seen at its source<a href="http://vimeo.com/10023990" target="_blank"> here</a> ,\n<h6><span style="color:#333399;"><em>(*music, The Beach Boys, "Sloop John B")\n<span style="color:#000000;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;">Thanks for viewing!</span></em></span></h6>', 'TERTIUM COMPARISON THE MOTION PICTURE', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '62', '', '', '2010-03-08 23:25:52', '2010-03-09 04:25:52', '', 0, 'http://seejbdraw.wordpress.com/2010/03/08/62/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(69, 2, '2010-03-18 12:27:47', '2010-03-18 17:27:47', 'Inspired by Hieronymus Bosch''s image by the same name.  These young chaps seem to be oblivious to the danger that surrounds them...kinda like some people in this world, right?\n\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/shipfools_blog.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-70" title="Ship of fools" src="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/shipfools_blog.jpg?w=300" alt="" width="300" height="222" /></a>\n\nThe final image is pretty large for me, about 22" x 30", and will be on display in May at my graduate thesis show here in NYC. More information to come on that...\n\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/shipfools_blog1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-71" title="close up 1" src="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/shipfools_blog1.jpg?w=300" alt="" width="300" height="254" /></a>\n\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/shipfools_blog1.jpg"></a><a href="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/shipfools_blog2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-72" title="close up 2" src="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/shipfools_blog2.jpg?w=300" alt="" width="300" height="291" /></a>', 'SHIP OF FOOLS', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ship-of-fools', '', '', '2010-03-18 12:27:47', '2010-03-18 17:27:47', '', 0, 'http://seejbdraw.wordpress.com/?p=69', 0, 'post', '', 3);
