(445, 2, '2011-07-05 15:46:48', '2011-07-05 20:46:48', '<a href="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/bartlett2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-446" title="bartlett2" src="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/bartlett2.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="260" /></a>\n\nTitle pretty much sums it up. I got a really fun call a few months back asking if I could illustrate Duke Nukem. I am not a video game player what so ever, but, like most other adolescent boys, I did dable in the first person shooter worlds back when things like Doom and Duke Nukem first came out for those old  PCs in the 90''s.  It wasn''t a big part of my daily life by any means, but Duke does bring back a few memories of childhood in Myrtle Beach, SC.  It made illustrating this picture all the more enjoyable.\n\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/barltett1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-447" title="barltett1" src="http://localhost:8888/jonathanbartlett/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/barltett1.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="251" /></a>\n\narticle here:<a href="http://www.wired.com/magazine/2011/06/pl_games_dukenukem/"> http://www.wired.com/magazine/2011/06/pl_games_dukenukem/</a>', 'DUKE NUKEM FOR WIRED', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'duke-nukem-for-wired', '', '', '2011-07-05 15:46:48', '2011-07-05 20:46:48', '', 0, 'http://seejbdraw.wordpress.com/?p=445', 0, 'post', '', 1),
